title: Ulmus parvifolia var. coreana
text:
Ulmus parvifolia" var. "coreana, the Korean elm, is a <a href="variety%20%28biology%29">variety</a> of the Chinese elm "<a href="Ulmus%20parvifolia">Ulmus parvifolia</a>", native to Korea.
Description.
Not available.
Pests and diseases.
No information available.
Cultivation.
The tree is very rare in cultivation in the United States and Europe. There are no known <a href="cultivar">cultivar</a>s of this taxon, nor is it known to be in commerce.
